) as expressed in a series of corn lines from March 1, 1994, to February 28, 1995. The amino acid sequence of the 

d

-endotoxin in corn was maintained to be identical to the amino acid sequence produced in 

Bacillus thuringiensis

. However, the nucleotide sequence of the cryIA(b) gene was modified to enhance expression in corn. In addition to
