assets, or the assets contributed to a joint venture by participants other than Columbia, is $1 million or less. Nor
would Paragraph III apply to joint ventures between Columbia and non-Columbia hospitals that are limited to the provision
of certain specified hospital support services (such as laundry or laboratory testing) or the establishment of new
health plans (such as health maintenance organizations). In addition, Paragraphs II and III would both expire ten
